{"article_id":"XbcjRsGlHWVhgAUa","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The administration likely wo n't meet its goal of 7 million sign-ups ,","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"but 6 million is possible .","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"Obamacare finally clears the tower","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"The Obamacare rollout is changing in front of our eyes -","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"turning from a running joke into one big shoulder shrug .","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"And that ' s good news for the White House ,","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"because at this point , even basic competence is good news .","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"That ' s the lesson of the new enrollment numbers","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"the administration released Monday ,","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"which showed","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"that more than 3 million people signed up for private health coverage under President Barack Obama ' s health care law by the end of January .","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"It ' s behind the original expectations ,","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"but way ahead of the disaster scenarios","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"that had looked possible during the worst months of the troubled rollout last fall .","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"There are still reasons","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"to be skeptical of the numbers ,","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"and health care experts warn","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"that the administration still has a lot of work to do by the end of March","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"- when enrollment ends for this year -","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"to get the right mix of customers","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"so there are enough healthy people","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"to pay for the sicker ones .","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"But the new report is good enough","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"that it might reset Washington ' s expectations :","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"maybe Obamacare isn ' t going to be a train wreck after all .","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"Maybe it ' ll be more like one of those Metro trains","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"that runs kind of slowly ,","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"and sometimes stops in the middle of the tracks for no apparent reason ,","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"but eventually gets you where you need to go .","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"Back in October , it looked like Obamacare enrollment could end up as a total bust .","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"Just 106,000 people had signed up ,","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"and it looked like a stretch to get even a few million by the end of March .","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"Now , the disaster scenario is already off the table .","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"By the end of January , 3.3 million Americans had selected a private health insurance plan .","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"That ' s a 1.1 million increase over the December figures ,","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"and it shows","depth":13},{"id":36,"text":"that people were still signing up at a pretty fast pace ,","depth":13},{"id":37,"text":"even though December was supposed to be one of the peak months","depth":13},{"id":38,"text":"as everyone rushed to sign up for January coverage .","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"The enrollment is now \" large enough","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"for the market to function , \"","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"said Jonathan Gruber , the MIT health economist","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"who consulted on Obamacare and the Massachusetts health reform law","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"that preceded it .","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"The first test","depth":13},{"id":45,"text":"the health care law had to pass","depth":13},{"id":46,"text":"was to get enough customers","depth":13},{"id":47,"text":"to avoid financial instability ,","depth":13},{"id":48,"text":"he said ,","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"and \" we ' re already past that . \"","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"And for once , HealthCare.gov","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"- the federal enrollment website","depth":13},{"id":52,"text":"that had the bungled launch -","depth":13},{"id":53,"text":"actually did better than the state-run websites .","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"The federal website ,","depth":13},{"id":55,"text":"which serves 36 states ,","depth":13},{"id":56,"text":"had a 62 percent increase in signups in January .","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"The state websites , in 14 states and the District of Columbia , only upped their numbers by 42 percent .","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"\" The federal marketplace finally seems to be getting its sea legs , \"","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"said Larry Levitt of the Kaiser Family Foundation .","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"Jon Kingsdale , a consultant","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"who ran the Massachusetts health insurance exchange","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"that became the model for Obamacare ,","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"called the new numbers \" very encouraging , \"","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"because it means","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"enrollment didn ' t slow down in January","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"as many analysts had expected .","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"It ' s also a sign","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"that enrollment could stay strong in February","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"and then surge in March","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"as enrollment ends ,","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"he said .","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"Of course , everything is about expectations","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"- which are lower now","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"than they were before the sputtering launch in October .","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"Are the numbers actually good ?","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"\" It essentially depends whether you ' re going to give them a pass on the first six weeks \"","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"when the federal website was essentially broken ,","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"said Gruber .","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"\" If you start the enrollment season in mid-November ,","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"than I think","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"it ' s outstanding .","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"If you start it in October ,","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"it still looks a little behind . \"","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"And for Obamacare critics , they ' re not good enough","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"to make up for the disasters of the early months .","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"\" That ' s why you talk about how you launched the beautiful new ocean liner ,","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"and then it hit the rocks ,","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"and then suddenly you ' re talking about how great it is that you got everyone off the ship","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"before it went down , \"","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"said Douglas Holtz-Eakin of the American Action Forum .","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"\" You have a different set of expectations","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"when it ' s a rescue operation . \"","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"They won ' t hit 7 million","depth":4},{"id":94,"text":"- but 6 million is doable","depth":4},{"id":95,"text":"No , the Obama administration is not on track","depth":6},{"id":96,"text":"to hit its original enrollment goal :","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"7 million people in the health insurance exchanges in the first year ,","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"based on the Congressional Budget Office projections","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"of how many they ' d get .","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"But","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"based on the new numbers ,","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"6 million isn ' t out of the question ,","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"independent analysts say .","depth":7},{"id":104,"text":"That ' s what CBO estimated in its newest projections ,","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"released last week ,","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"after it factored in all the website problems during the troubled launch .","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"\" Enrollment appears on-track to reach roughly 6 million by the end of March , \"","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"said Caroline Pearson , vice president at the Avalere Health consulting firm .","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"Levitt said","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"the Obama administration \" could very easily reach or exceed \" 6 million","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"- but it depends how much outreach it ' s able to do in the last two months of enrollment ,","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"he said ,","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"as well as how much insurers are willing to spend on advertising","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"to attract as many customers","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"as they can get .","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"Two important points the new numbers don ' t tell us , though :","depth":6},{"id":117,"text":"How many of these customers were uninsured before ,","depth":7},{"id":118,"text":"and how many are just replacing health insurance policies","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"that were canceled","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"because of , well , Obamacare .","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"On a conference call with reporters , Obama administration officials said","depth":7},{"id":122,"text":"they don ' t have that information .","depth":7},{"id":123,"text":"But not to worry ,","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"they said -","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"they ' re focused on getting as many people to sign up","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"as they possibly can .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":253,"left":128,"right":252,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":128,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":252,"left":218,"right":251,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":218,"left":2,"right":217,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":217,"left":153,"right":216,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":153,"left":138,"right":152,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":138,"left":131,"right":137,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":131,"left":